module.exports = /*#__PURE__*/JSON.parse('{"nav":{"home":"Home","principles":"Principles","research":"Research","founder":"Our Founder","login":"Login","logout":"Logout","dashboard":"Dashboard"},"home":{"headline":"A Twenty-Year Horizon","subtitle":"Long-duration digital asset investment grounded in first principles and institutional discipline.","body":"2ØY Fund is structured around a single conviction: that transformative value in digital assets requires time, patience, and rigorous intellectual frameworks. We invest with a twenty-year horizon and manage with the seriousness that conviction demands.","links":{"heading":"Explore Our Framework","principles":"Investment Principles","research":"Research & Analysis","founder":"About Our Founder"}},"principles":{"title":"Investment Principles","card1":{"heading":"Long Duration as Strategy","body":"Most market participants are structurally constrained to short time horizons. We treat duration itself as a competitive advantage — holding through cycles that eliminate shorter-term players and compounding the insights that only time reveals."},"card2":{"heading":"First-Principles Analysis","body":"We avoid consensus thinking. Each position is built from the ground up through independent analysis of protocol economics, network dynamics, and adoption curves. We seek to understand before we allocate."},"card3":{"heading":"Institutional Discipline","body":"Rigorous portfolio construction, defined risk parameters, and systematic review processes. We apply the same analytical standards to digital assets that define best-in-class traditional asset management."},"card4":{"heading":"Concentrated Conviction","body":"Diversification without understanding is speculation. We hold a small number of positions sized by conviction, not by fear of being wrong. Concentration amplifies research alpha and forces intellectual honesty."}},"founder":{"title":"Our Founder","name":"Ibai Basabe","credentials":"Math PhD, University of Florida · AI & Music, College of Charleston · Concert Pianist · Researcher, Medical University of South Carolina · Founder, 2ØY Fund","p1":"Growing up on the northern coast of the Iberian peninsula, he was the odd boy in town — drawn to piano, chess, and coin collecting rather than the sports that occupied his peers. A grandmother\'s gift of old coins sparked an early fascination with numismatics and the question of what gives money its value. These were not questions he would let go.","p2":"At seventeen, a full piano scholarship brought him to America. He earned degrees in classical piano and mathematics, later adding advanced graduate work. The pairing was not incidental: he has always understood both disciplines as systems for finding structure in chaos, coherence in complexity.","p3":"In 2013, an article about Bitcoin stopped him. He read Satoshi Nakamoto\'s whitepaper in a single sitting. The mathematics were elegant, the implications enormous. He began accumulating Bitcoin early, received a job offer from Coinbase, and in 2014 traveled to the Miami Bitcoin Conference — where a young Vitalik Buterin stood on stage and announced Ethereum to the world.","p4":"The following years took him through directing a mathematics school and conducting orchestras before relocating to Shanghai in 2017. There he joined BitSE, working alongside the teams building Qtum and VeChain during one of the most consequential cycles in the asset class\'s history. The experience confirmed what the whitepaper had suggested: this was not a passing curiosity but a structural shift.","p5":"The fund\'s name comes from a vision in 2019, in which three symbols appeared: 2ØY. Two for duality. Ø for the empty set — the mathematical origin, the void from which structure emerges. Y for curiosity and the branching logic of inquiry. That image became the organizing principle for everything that followed.","p6":"Mathematics and music remain his twin frameworks. Both impose order on unpredictability. Both reward patience and precision. It is the same disposition he brings to long-duration digital asset investing: a conviction that understanding precedes allocation, that time is an asset, and that discipline — not speed — is the sustainable edge."},"research":{"title":"Research & Analysis","intro":"Independent research grounded in first-principles analysis of digital asset protocols, network economics, and long-duration investment frameworks.","backLink":"← Back to Research","noArticles":"No research published yet. Check back soon."},"dashboard":{"title":"Investor Dashboard","investmentSummary":{"heading":"Investment Summary","amount":"Investment Amount","investmentDate":"Investment Date","liquidationDate":"Liquidation Date","lockRemaining":"Lock Period Remaining","status":"Status"},"wallet":{"heading":"Wallet Information","address":"Wallet Address"},"documents":{"heading":"Documents"},"notFound":"Investor record not found."},"auth":{"login":{"title":"Investor Login","email":"Email Address","password":"Password","submit":"Sign In","error":"Invalid credentials. Please try again.","serverError":"Login service unavailable. Please try again later."}},"footer":{"confidential":"Confidential — For Accredited Investors Only","colNavigate":"Navigate","colConnect":"Connect","colSubscribe":"Subscribe","newsletter":{"description":"Updates on research and fund announcements.","placeholder":"Email address","button":"Subscribe"}}}');

